author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
New York City is emerging as the center of the nation’s office-to-residential conversion boom, proving these projects can go far beyond what many thought possible.⁠
⁠
Office-to-home conversions picked up after the pandemic, and architectural hacks pioneered in Manhattan will likely accelerate the pace across the country.⁠

title: How Open Offices Are Converted to Apartments in New York City
